      "source": [
        "## Programación Dinámica. Viaje por el rio\n",
        "* **Definición**: Es posible dividir el problema en subproblemas más pequeños, guardando las soluciones para ser utilizadas más adelante.\n",
        "* **Características** que permiten identificar problemas aplicables:<br>\n",
        "  -Es posible almacenar soluciones de los subproblemas para ser utilizados más adelante<br>\n",
        "  -Debe verificar el principio de optimalidad de Bellman: “en una secuencia optima de decisiones, toda sub-secuencia también es óptima” (*)<br>\n",
        "  -La necesidad de guardar la información acerca de las soluciones parciales unido a la recursividad provoca la necesidad de preocuparnos por la complejidad espacial (cuantos recursos de espacio usaremos)<br>\n",
        "\n",
        "### Problema<br>\n",
        "En un río hay **n** embarcaderos y debemos desplazarnos río abajo desde un embarcadero a otro. Cada embarcadero tiene precios diferentes para ir de un embarcadero a otro situado más abajo. Para ir del embarcadero i al j, puede ocurrir que sea más barato hacer un trasbordo por un embarcadero intermedio k. El problema consiste en determinar la combinación más barata.\n",
        "\n",
        "![1.jpg](data:image/jpeg;base64,)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "S_LCFW3123Xc"
      },
      "source": [
        "* Resuelve el problema del descenso por el rio utilizando la técnica de optimización que consideres más adecuada."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "precios = np.array([0,5,4,3,0,0,0,0,0,0,2,3,0,11,0,0,0,1,0,4,10,0,0,0,0,5,6,9,0,0,0,0,0,0,4,0,0,0,0,0,0,3]).reshape(6,7)\n",
        "display(precios)\n",
        "\n",
        "def esMinimo(columna):\n",
        "  valores_distintos_de_cero = columna[columna != 0]\n",
        "  if valores_distintos_de_cero.size > 0:\n",
        "      valor_minimo = np.min(valores_distintos_de_cero)\n",
        "      return valor_minimo\n",
        "  else:\n",
        "      return False\n",
        "\n",
        "nuevoNodo = 6\n",
        "costoActual = 0\n",
        "ruta = '6'\n",
        "\n",
        "while(nuevoNodo != 0):\n",
        "  costoAsumar = esMinimo(precios[:,nuevoNodo])\n",
        "  siguienteNodo = np.where(precios[:,nuevoNodo] == esMinimo(precios[:,nuevoNodo]))[0][0]\n",
        "\n",
        "  ruta += '->' + str(siguienteNodo)\n",
        "  nuevoNodo = siguienteNodo\n",
        "  costoActual += costoAsumar\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"La ruta más eficiente es {ruta}, cuyo coste fue de: {costoActual}\")\n"
      ],

        "#Definimos la funcion\n",
        "#Paraboloide\n",
        "f  = lambda X:      X[0]**2 + X[1]**2    #Funcion\n",
        "df = lambda X: [2*X[0] , 2*X[1]]         #Gradiente\n",

        "#Prepara los datos para dibujar mapa de niveles de Z\n",
        "resolucion = 100\n",
        "rango=5.5\n",
        "\n",
        "X=np.linspace(-rango,rango,resolucion)\n",
        "Y=np.linspace(-rango,rango,resolucion)\n",
        "Z=np.zeros((resolucion,resolucion))\n",
        "for ix,x in enumerate(X):\n",
        "  for iy,y in enumerate(Y):\n",
        "    Z[iy,ix] = f([x,y])\n",
        "\n",
        "#Pinta el mapa de niveles de Z\n",
        "plt.contourf(X,Y,Z,resolucion)\n",
        "plt.colorbar()\n",
        "\n",
        "#Generamos un punto aleatorio inicial y pintamos de blanco\n",
        "P=[random.uniform(-5,5  ),random.uniform(-5,5 ) ]\n",
        "plt.plot(P[0],P[1],\"o\",c=\"white\")\n",
        "\n",
        "#Tasa de aprendizaje. Fija. Sería más efectivo reducirlo a medida que nos acercamos.\n",
        "TA=1\n",
        "\n",
        "#Iteraciones:50\n",
        "for _ in range(1000):\n",
        "  grad = df(P)\n",
        "  #print(P,grad)\n",
        "  P[0],P[1] = P[0] - TA*grad[0] , P[1] - TA*grad[1]\n",
        "  plt.plot(P[0],P[1],\"o\",c=\"red\")\n",
        "\n",
        "#Dibujamos el punto final y pintamos de verde\n",
        "plt.plot(P[0],P[1],\"o\",c=\"green\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "print(\"Solucion:\" , P , f(P))\n"
      ]

      "source": [
        "## Reto\n",
        "\n",
        "Optimizar la función siguiente mediante el algoritmo por descenso del gradiente.\n",
        "\n",
        "$$f(x)=sin(1/2 * x^2 - 1/4 * y^2 + 3) * cos(2*x + 1 - e^y)$$\n",
        "<br>\n",
        "![2.png](data:image/png;base64,)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 55,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "D2lcBPMKFjkT"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "#Definimos la funcion\n",
        "import math\n",
        "f = lambda X: math.sin(1/2 * X[0]**2 - 1/4 * X[1]**2 + 3) *math.cos(2*X[0] + 1 - math.exp(X[1]) )\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sympy import symbols, sin, cos, exp\n",
        "from sympy.plotting import plot3d\n",
        "\n",
        "# Definir los símbolos\n",
        "x, y = symbols('x y')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Definir la función usando los símbolos\n",
        "f = sin(1/2 * x**2 - 1/4 * y**2 + 3) * cos(2 * x + 1 - exp(y))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Graficar la función en 3D\n",
        "plot3d(f, (x, -5, 5), (y, -5, 5), title='f(x, y) = sin(1/2 * x^2 - 1/4 * y^2 + 3) * cos(2*x + 1 - exp(y))', size=(10, 10))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 1000
        },
        "id": "PjPvw5obS4xO",
        "outputId": "d79b7b6a-307e-4478-eba5-6c8fd662b4f3"
      },
      "execution_count": 56,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1000x1000 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<sympy.plotting.plot.Plot at 0x79b33375e050>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 56
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Sea la función:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(x, y) = \\sin\\left(\\frac{1}{2} x^2 - \\frac{1}{4} y^2 + 3\\right) \\cdot \\cos\\left(2x + 1 - e^y\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "La derivada parcial de $f$ con respecto a $x$ es:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial x} = \\cos\\left(\\frac{1}{2} x^2 - \\frac{1}{4} y^2 + 3\\right) \\cdot x \\cdot \\cos\\left(2x + 1 - e^y\\right) - 2 \\sin\\left(\\frac{1}{2} x^2 - \\frac{1}{4} y^2 + 3\\right) \\cdot \\sin\\left(2x + 1 - e^y\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "La derivada parcial de $f$ con respecto a $y$ es:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial y} = -\\frac{1}{2} y \\cos\\left(\\frac{1}{2} x^2 - \\frac{1}{4} y^2 + 3\\right) \\cdot \\cos\\left(2x + 1 - e^y\\right) + e^y \\sin\\left(\\frac{1}{2} x^2 - \\frac{1}{4} y^2 + 3\\right) \\cdot \\sin\\left(2x + 1 - e^y\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WW0Dv2dFQDFV"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import math\n",
        "\n",
        "# Función original\n",
        "f = lambda X: math.sin(1/2 * X[0]**2 - 1/4 * X[1]**2 + 3) * math.cos(2 * X[0] + 1 - math.exp(X[1]))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Derivada parcial con respecto a x\n",
        "df_dx = lambda X: (\n",
        "    math.cos(1/2 * X[0]**2 - 1/4 * X[1]**2 + 3) * X[0] * math.cos(2 * X[0] + 1 - math.exp(X[1])) -\n",
        "    2 * math.sin(1/2 * X[0]**2 - 1/4 * X[1]**2 + 3) * math.sin(2 * X[0] + 1 - math.exp(X[1]))\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Derivada parcial con respecto a y\n",
        "df_dy = lambda X: (\n",
        "    -1/2 * X[1] * math.cos(1/2 * X[0]**2 - 1/4 * X[1]**2 + 3) * math.cos(2 * X[0] + 1 - math.exp(X[1])) +\n",
        "    math.exp(X[1]) * math.sin(1/2 * X[0]**2 - 1/4 * X[1]**2 + 3) * math.sin(2 * X[0] + 1 - math.exp(X[1]))\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Función gradiente\n",
        "gradient = lambda X: [df_dx(X), df_dy(X)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ejemplo de uso:\n",
        "X = [1.0, 2.0]  # Ejemplo de valores para x e y\n",
        "gradiente_valores = gradient(X)\n",
        "print(\"Gradiente en X:\", gradiente_valores)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "kn5qbo1eQmhz",
        "outputId": "11ac077d-ae9f-4b4a-a07f-04ef8fc7c1e3"
      },
      "execution_count": 57,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Gradiente en X: [-0.8803745550791662, 3.9384502467765357]\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import random\n",
        "\n",
        "# Prepara los datos para dibujar el mapa de niveles de Z\n",
        "resolucion = 100\n",
        "rango = 5.5\n",
        "\n",
        "X = np.linspace(-rango, rango, resolucion)\n",
        "Y = np.linspace(-rango, rango, resolucion)\n",
        "Z = np.zeros((resolucion, resolucion))\n",
        "\n",
        "for ix, x in enumerate(X):\n",
        "    for iy, y in enumerate(Y):\n",
        "        Z[iy, ix] = f([x, y])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pinta el mapa de niveles de Z\n",
        "plt.contourf(X, Y, Z, resolucion)\n",
        "plt.colorbar()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generamos un punto aleatorio inicial y pintamos de blanco\n",
        "P = [random.uniform(-5, 5), random.uniform(-5, 5)]\n",
        "plt.plot(P[0], P[1], \"o\", c=\"white\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tasa de aprendizaje. Fija. Sería más efectivo reducirlo a medida que nos acercamos.\n",
        "TA = 0.01  # Reduce la tasa de aprendizaje para evitar saltos grandes\n",
        "\n",
        "# Iteraciones\n",
        "for _ in range(1000):\n",
        "    grad = gradient(P)\n",
        "    P[0], P[1] = P[0] - TA * grad[0], P[1] - TA * grad[1]\n",
        "    plt.plot(P[0], P[1], \"o\", c=\"red\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Dibujamos el punto final y pintamos de verde\n",
        "plt.plot(P[0], P[1], \"o\", c=\"green\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Solución:\", P, f(P))\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 447
        },
        "id": "8AhDvR7dRilf",
        "outputId": "76f4616e-7f3a-43a1-f049-351f33fd7610"
      },

        "# Conclusión final: desplegar el óptimo encontrado\n",
        "print(\"Solución óptima encontrada:\")\n",
        "print(\"Punto: \", P)\n",
        "print(\"Valor de la función en el punto óptimo: \", f(P))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mensaje de conclusión\n",
        "print(\"\\nEl algoritmo de descenso de gradiente ha convergido a un punto cerca de\", P, \"con un valor de función de\", f(P))\n",
        "print(\"Esto sugiere que este punto es un óptimo local de la función en el rango dado.\")"

              "    async function download(id, filename, size) {\n",
              "      if (!google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed) {\n",
              "        return;\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      const div = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "      const label = document.createElement('label');\n",
              "      label.textContent = `Downloading \"${filename}\": `;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(label);\n",
              "      const progress = document.createElement('progress');\n",
              "      progress.max = size;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(progress);\n",
              "      document.body.appendChild(div);\n",
              "\n",
              "      const buffers = [];\n",
              "      let downloaded = 0;\n",
              "\n",
              "      const channel = await google.colab.kernel.comms.open(id);\n",
              "      // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n",
              "      channel.send({})\n",
              "\n",
              "      for await (const message of channel.messages) {\n",
              "        // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n",
              "        channel.send({})\n",
              "        if (message.buffers) {\n",
              "          for (const buffer of message.buffers) {\n",
              "            buffers.push(buffer);\n",
              "            downloaded += buffer.byteLength;\n",
              "            progress.value = downloaded;\n",
              "          }\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      const blob = new Blob(buffers, {type: 'application/binary'});\n",
              "      const a = document.createElement('a');\n",
              "      a.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n",
              "      a.download = filename;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(a);\n",
              "      a.click();\n",
              "      div.remove();\n",
              "    }\n",
              "  "
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
